This paper deals with image quality assessment using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper focuses on high dynamic range (HDR) images, which are often used in multimedia applications (cs.MM). The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses perceptual masking effects, which are related to human perception and could fall under graphics (cs.GR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
